n. Dieses Phänomen betrifft tief verwurzelte Arbeits-, Kommunikations- und Wahrnehmungsweisen, generationelle Erfahrungs- und Erwartungshorizonte, konventionalisierte Medienmentalitäten und -kulturen. Deren Konstellation versucht dieses Buch nachzuzeichnen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCivilization, Moderny20th century. 4aFlüchtigkeit. 4aMediengeschichte. 4aMedientheorie. 4aMedienumbrüche. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMedienästhetik. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia History.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia Theory.1 aDobbe, Martina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErstić, Marijana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarncarz, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGendolla, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrauer, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHülk, Walburga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHüser, Gisela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKäuser, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLommel, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLück, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchnell, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchnell, Ralf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchröter, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStanitzek, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStanitzek, Georg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUhl, Matthias, eco